OL,3,CCourt of Appeal refuses to change
OL,4,CNottingham attacks killer's sentence
OL,6,FThe Court of Appeal has refused to
OL,7,Fchange the sentence of the Nottingham
OL,8,Fattacks killer, Valdo Calocane, who
OL,9,Fwas given an indefinite hospital order
OL,10,Ffor the manslaughter of three people.
OL,12,Ffor the manslaughter by reason of
OL,13,Fdiminished responsibility of Barnaby
OL,14,FWebber, Grace O'Malley-Kumar and Ian
OL,15,FCoates, and the attempted murder of
OL,16,Fthree others in Nottingham in June
OL,17,Flast year.
