OL,6,FThe Attorney General referred the
OL,7,Fsentence to the Court of Appeal,
OL,8,Fclaiming his indefinite hospital order
OL,9,Fwas 'unduly lenient'.
OL,11,FA hearing at the Court of Appeal on
OL,12,FTuesday 14 May was told: "Neither the
OL,13,Fjudge nor this court can ignore the
OL,14,Fmedical evidence as to the offender's
OL,15,Fcondition which led to these dreadful
OL,16,Fevents or the threat to public safety
OL,17,Fwhich the offender continues to pose."
